    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>Once Bitcoin has been broadly accepted as a viable alternative to gold, just better, digital notes backed by Bitcoin will one day be issued. But that backing will be real and verifiable by the network and the supply and cost of credit can be driven, as they should be, by free market forces not some deluded central banker.</p>

    	</div>



