        <li data-comment-id="comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/2060-1225-187" data-comment-wp-id="187"  parent-id="" class="comment level0 calledOut" data-badges-advoice="">
            <div class="entity_block">
                <a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/sgornick/">
                    <img src="http://blogs-images.forbes.com/cache/gravatars/sgornick_40.jpg" alt="sgornick" />
                </a>



                <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/sgornick/">
                    sgornick
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">2 years ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>Those shopping at Publix this week learned what happens when your ability to spend depends on a third party that might not always be reliable — you don’t eat.</p> 
<p>– http://landolakes.patch.com/articles/publix-sweetbay-experiencing-problems-with-debit-cards-0477f066</p> 
<p>Those who had funds with MF Global learned that there are risks no matter which party is holding your cash.</p> 
<p>But even holding physical cash yourself has risks — ask those in Greece seeing a rising residential burglary rate.</p> 
<p>Bitcoin is the only type of money that does not use any third party for storage yet also can be secured simply (with a passphrase).</p> 
<p>This capability is just as beneficial to the person where $50 is a “large balance” as it is to the person that sits at the high roller table.</p>

    	</div>



